quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
4,114,"Most of their secret conferrings are devoid of good, unless one secretly enjoins in charity, good deeds, and setting the affairs of men right. We shall grant who ever does that seeking to please Allah a great reward."
4,115,"As for him who sets himself against the Messenger and follows a path other than that of the believers even after true guidance had become clear to him, We will let him go to the way he has turned to, {1} and We will cast him into Hell - an evil destination.",footnotes:1:When
4,116,"Truly it is only associating others with Allah in His divinity that Allah does not forgive, {1} and forgives anything besides that to whomsoever He wills. Whoever associates others with Allah in His divinity has indeed strayed far away.",footnotes:1:In this and the following verses we are asked to consider coolly
4,117,"Rather than call upon Him, they call upon goddesses, and call upon a rebellious Satan {1}",footnotes:1:No one sets up Satan as his 'god' in the sense that he makes him the object of his ritual worship and declares him to be God in so many words. The way to make Satan one's god is to entrust one's reins to him and let oneself be drawn helplessly in whichever direction he wants; the relationship between the two is
4,118,"upon whom Allah has laid His curse. He said (to Allah): 'I will take to myself an appointed portion of Your servants {1}",footnotes:1:This shows that Satan is determined to lay his claim to a portion of men's time
4,119,"and shall lead them astray, and shall engross them in vain desires, and I shall command them and they will cut off the ears of the cattle, {1} and I shall command them and they will disfigure Allah's creation.' {2} He who took Satan rather than Allah for his guardian has indeed suffered a man-ifest loss.",footnotes:1:The reference here is to a superstitious Arabian custom. It was customary among the Arabs that after a camel had given birth to five or ten young to slit her ears and let her go in the name of their deity; they considered it forbidden to put her to any work. Likewise
4,120,"Satan makes promises to them and fills them with vain hopes, {1} but whatever he promises them is merely delusion.",footnotes:1:Satanic operations are based on making attractive promises and raising high hopes. Whenever Satan wants to mislead men
4,121,"For these people, their abode shall be Hell and from there they shall find no way of escape."
